By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  Nigeria has recorded 156 new cases of COVID-19, bringing the total confirmed cases to 64,884, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control said. The NCDC stated this in the report it released via twitter handle late Friday night. According to the report, the 156 new infections were recorded from 11 states including the FCT as follows; Lagos-70FCT-22Kaduna-18Rivers-15Plateau-11Ogun-10Bauchi-3Katsina-3Kano-2Ekiti-1Osun-1 The health agency also stated that 60,936 patients have been discharged from across the various isolation facilities in the country since the index case while 1,163 lives have been lost to the COVID-19 related ailments. See the state by state breakdown of total confirmed cases below: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The total confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Nigeria hit 59,001 as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) reported 153 new fresh infections on Thursday. Similarly, the NCDC report released via it's twitter handle account further said that the total of 50, 452… October 2, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Plateau state on Tuesday led the COVID-19 infection table with 50 patients as new confirmed cases dropped to 252, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has said. The health agency which released the report via it's twitter handle said these new confirmed cases… August 26, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -  Lagos State, the epicentre of COVID-19 in Nigeria recorded 106 infections on Friday as the Centre for Disease Control confirmed 170 new cases of the novel virus. This renewed upsurge in number of infections in Lagos may not be unconnected with the large… October 31, 2020 In "Top Stories"